    "output_text": "We are asked to solve the system of equations:\n\n2x + 2y = 6\n3x - y = 5\n\nWe need to find x and y.\n\nWe can solve by substitution or elimination. Let's do elimination.\n\nFirst, simplify the first equation: divide both sides by 2: x + y = 3. So we have:\n\n(1) x + y = 3\n(2) 3x - y = 5\n\nNow add the two equations: (x + y) + (3x - y) = 3 + 5 => 4x = 8 => x = 2.\n\nSubstitute x = 2 into (1): 2 + y = 3 => y = 1.\n\nCheck with (2): 3(2) - 1 = 6 - 1 = 5, correct.\n\nThus solution: x = 2, y = 1.\n\nWe can present as: \\boxed{x=2,\\ y=1}.</think>The solution to the system of equations is \\(x = 2\\) and \\(y = 1\\).\n\n\\boxed{x=2,\\ y=1}",
